{"word":"λέκτρον","slug":"λέκτρον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λέκτρον</b></el> <el>(λέκτρον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:λέγω'><el>λέγω1</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:λέχος'><el>λέχος</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a couch, bed</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>lectus</el>, in sg. and <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>λέκτρονδε</el> <i>to bed</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>the marriage-bed</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>ἀλλότρια, νόθα, λέκτρα</el>, of illicit connexions, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}